23/05/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Former Republika Srpska (RS) Army member Momir Savic is facing an international warrant for his arrest, the Court of BiH confirmed on Saturday (May 22nd). 
In 2009, Savic was found guilty of crimes against humanity committed against Bosniaks in Visegrad during the 1992-1995 war. 
According to local press reports, Savic fled on May 18th, a day after the appeals chamber of the court cut his sentence from 18 to 17 years in prison. 
(Tanjug, BHRT, Srna, RTRS - 22/05/10)
